"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## I know what you’re thinking, but hear me out, if only so I can tell you about Yatreda, Noah Kalina, and Julie Blackmon\\n\\n[![Ellis Brooks](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/1\\\\*ksNauGSJWBQ7Ic5iEjldrw.jpeg)](https://ellisbrooks.medium.com/?source=post_page-----47229311dcf8-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://ellisbrooks.medium.com/?source=post_page-----47229311dcf8-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Ellis Brooks](https://ellisbrooks.medium.com/?source=post_page-----47229311dcf8-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://onezero.medium.com/nfts-are-critical-for-the-future-of-art-47229311dcf8?source=post_page-----47229311dcf8-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Dec 17·15 min read](https://onezero.medium.com/nfts-are-critical-for-the-future-of-art-47229311dcf8?source=post_page-----47229311dcf8-----------------------------------)\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/2000/1\\\\*aPkFNkXw3EWt1PTLsX4GTA.png)\\n\\n**Julie Blackmon**, Homegrown Food (2012). Pigment print available at [Edelman Gallery](https://www.edelmangallery.com/artists/artists/a-f/julie-blackmon.html#?id=77). Also minted as an NFT and listed at [Quantum](https://www.quantum.art/collection/homegrown).\\n\\nMultiple things can be true at once, even when they appear to be contradictory. Granite, for example, can be both solid and ethereal. Hold a chunk of it in the palm of your hand and it’s clearly a…\\n\",\"timestamp\":1640454075,\"title\":\"NFTs Are Critical for the Future of Art - OneZero\"},\"digest\":\"L6P5wFoKycsoNct_tpfhAtf3YvlWJYxEoc3HqyIORO8\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x5935cf67Ba7A9d90A4d1Ce30787B268ba79863DB\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"AUOCCUNEJ491iUICsDkppjnMeWfrlyb-mi9mjz1mpPM\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"q89nKfK-GsDtDP_8lyWjAGs-bJBnsAAVvRS0QnwCVV8\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"csf2_ndwFlRbzPV06K5NkW7BFOfF4i04tDoaPnW1qFducu5ktDyq